title: For Sale/Trade:  120 Round Box of Practice & Defend Ammo 100 Ball/20 Hydra-Shok
postcontent:
Train Like You're Going to Fight.
If you practice with "Managed Recoil" loads, what's going to happen when you have to shoot those full power hollow points you carry?  Will you be surprised by the recoil? You might not be holding the pistol tightly enough.  

Then again, you don't want to spend dump money into the backstop at the range by shooting hollow points for practice either.  

I have a single sealed box of 120 rounds of Federal .45 ACP ammo.  It really is an ingenious concept.  If you've just bought a .45 and need to practice with it before it becomes your CCW gun, this is a perfect deal.  If you just want some practice ammunition and some jacketed hollow point ammo for defense, it's a good deal, too.  Otherwise you could buy this one box and add to your overall supply of practice and defense ammo.

Both the practice ammo and the defense ammo are 230 grain bullets, so theoretically, you'll have the same recoil, muzzle flip and recovery in practice as you will get if you ever have to fire the Hydra-Shok defense ammo, when your life may depend on that second or third round.

The Bear Domain is one bow below the Method in Bear's bow line up. Although the Method is only $50 more on its MSRP there are many differences. The Bear Method is a dual cam bow and is 18 fps faster on its IBO. The Domain, however, is a more comfortable and forgiving bow to shoot. It seems to be a little more of a "hunting" bow, although either would work fine for hunting. The Method has 5% less let off and .25" less brace height. Their weights are the same. The Domain is what a hunting bow is. It will be more than able to harvest any big game that one could hunt. Recreational 3D shooting would also be fine for this bow and would probably satisfy the majority of shooters. It has great comfort, decent speed, and is very easy to adjust to fit a large range of shooters. Archers on a budget, entry level or experienced could find this bow just right for them.

title: For Sale/Trade:  A-TACS Camo top and bottom and boonie NWOT uniform set
postcontent:
I have a new with out tags A-TACS (Advanced Tactical Concealment System) for sale. It includes the Top, bottom, and boonie hat. The set normally sells for over $130 so my loss is your gain. The sizes are Top M-L 71in -74in tall 37in-40in chest, bottoms are M-R 31in-34in waist 29 1/2in - 32 1/2in inseam. The hat is 7 3/4. Price is firm. Below is a write up from their website if you are unfamiliar with A-TACS.

A-TACS is a new and radical advancement in camo design and technology. Most digital camo patterns use small square pixels. A-TACS by way of comparison uses very small organically shaped pixels. The end result is that all the hard 90 degree angles of a typical pixel are removed which creates a camo pattern that has a more natural appearance.

Taking this process a step further the small organically shaped pixels are placed within larger groupings to create a "pattern within a pattern". This radical advancement means that A-TACS is able to conceal the operator far more effectively and at greater distances vs many other camo patterns.

The line of A-TACS ACUs from Propper will be made to military specifications. The initial line of clothing will be made from a 65/35 poly/cotton ripstop fabric which is designed for maximum durability.

title: For Sale:  SKS Detachable Magazines (DC Eng. plus RARE CHINESE PROTOTYPE)
postcontent:
I've been collecting these over the past few years because I know they are the best and most reliable (and easily adjusted) of all the detachable SKS mags.  The one on the far left (with the ribs) actually has the word "CHINA" stamped on it.  The long one with the ribs on the right has DC Eng. stamped on it.  The two long mags in the middle are both DC Eng. and the short one on the far right has no markings. 

These are the most reliable due to the heavy gauge metal construction plus the easiest to adjust because of the single flat bar in front.  Most know that these sometimes have feed lip alignment issues.  Don't try to adjust the lips themselves, just bend the flat bars (front or back) to bring the lips into alignment with the receiver.

postcontent: The "Sturmgewer" (Assault Rifle) is the semi auto rifle that Mikhail Kalashnikov found on the ground in Russia during WWII.  He was so impressed with its capabilities that he kept one and studied its design.  During his time spent at a military hospital he drew blueprints and eventually created the AK-47.  But this gun is the one that started it all.  A German design that wasn't allowed to be mass produced by Hitler.  This firearm has the size and weight of the original while being chambered in .22LR.
